install tools using make command. This will install all tools, dependencies and build the project.\n  4. Run the server using ./bin/twirp-server or using the 'Run and Debug' launch menu in VS code.\n\nImportant\n\nYou need to re-build the files and restart the server if you have done any\ncode changes in the project.\n\n### Example Usage\n\n#### Go Client\n\n    \n    \n    ./bin/twirp-client\n\n#### cURL\n\nOnce the service is running, you can make RPC requests to it using a Twirp\nclient. Here's an example using cURL:\n\n    \n    \n    curl -X POST \\ -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\ -d '{\"inches\": 10}' \\ http://localhost:8080/twirp/service.Haberdasher/MakeHat | jq\n\n## About\n\nThis is a Twirp sample service with ready to go development environment.\n\n### Resources\n\nReadme\n\nActivity\n\n### Stars\n\n1 star\n\n### Watchers\n\n1 watching\n\n### Forks\n\n0 forks\n\nReport repository\n\n## Releases\n\nNo releases published\n\n## Packages 0\n\nNo packages published\n\n## Languages\n\n  * Go 45.2%\n  * Shell 18.9%\n  * Dockerfile 18.8%\n  * Makefile 17.1%\n\n## Footer\n\n\u00a9 2024 GitHub, Inc.\n\nYou can\u2019t perform that action at this time.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
